      "writtenOn": "2018-12-04T00:42:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Nope - I left this in here because I feel it would be quite logical to add a button or radio selector to allow the user to switch between wide and narrow mode on this somewhat irritatingly complex function shows how to do that - didn\u0027t want later author to have to figure out how to cook this up from scratch.\n\n(This selection could be similar to the * Expanded * Default * Non-Green selection on the results page)\n\nShould I remove the function completely or add a widget to flip between wide and narrow? (Right now it chooses by initial page render screen width.) Or perhaps remove and forget the widget. Note that Nodir also had a comment pertaining to screen width / tab rendering below.",
      "parentUuid": "d4cff967_f8352037",
      "revId": "caab85964662c83f66e4bbcb0dd2739322cf5583",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
