      },
      "lineNbr": 137,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-03T20:21:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think this tries to add column class to results-tab and properties twice.\nAlso this is inconsistent with L134\n\nI think you meant\n\n $(\u0027#results, #results-tab, #properties, #changes\u0027).addClass(\u0027column\u0027)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 135,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 137,
        "endChar": 50
      },
      "revId": "caab85964662c83f66e4bbcb0dd2739322cf5583",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "09bf7829_a3041482",
        "filename": "milo/frontend/appengine/static/common/js/build.js",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 137,
      "author": {
        "id": 1297361
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-04T00:42:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No the #results-tab itself doesn\u0027t get the class. It is actually equivalent to this:\n\n$(\u0027#results, #properties, #changes\u0027).addClass(\u0027column\u0027);\n$(\u0027#results-tab\u0027)\n    .append($(\u0027#properties\u0027))\n    .append($(\u0027#changes\u0027));\n\nbut that has jQuery looking up two of the elements twice. Minor - but still.",
      "parentUuid": "f5dbe851_4958338e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 135,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 137,
        "endChar": 50
      },
      "revId": "caab85964662c83f66e4bbcb0dd2739322cf5583",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
